## ğŸ’¡ Built-in Hints

### **Hint 1: VLSM Golden Rule**
> Always allocate largest subnets first! This prevents address space fragmentation.

### **Hint 2: Subnet Mask Selection**
> To find the right mask:
> 1. Round hosts up to nearest power of 2
> 2. Add 2 for network + broadcast
> 3. Use formula: 2^(host bits) - 2 â‰¥ hosts needed

### **Hint 3: Next Subnet Address**
> Network Address + Subnet Size = Next Network
> Example: 192.168.1.0/25 (128 IPs) â†’ Next: 192.168.1.128

---

## ğŸ“ "Show Math" Feature

Click "Show Math" to see step-by-step calculations:

```
ğŸ“ Calculation Breakdown

Step 1: Find smallest power of 2 â‰¥ 120
â†’ 2^7 = 128 (âœ“)

Step 2: Subtract 2 for network + broadcast
â†’ 128 - 2 = 126 usable hosts

Step 3: Calculate subnet mask
â†’ Need 7 host bits (2^7 = 128)
â†’ 32 - 7 = 25 network bits
â†’ Subnet Mask: /25

Step 4: Next subnet starts at
â†’ 192.168.1.0 + 128 = 192.168.1.128
```

