## ğŸ“ Pedagogical Approach

### **Learning Principles Used**

1. **Learning by Doing** - Hands-on subnet allocation
2. **Immediate Feedback** - Instant validation of choices
3. **Progressive Difficulty** - Easy â†’ Medium â†’ Hard
4. **Visual Learning** - See address space allocation
5. **Gamification** - Scores, grades, achievements
6. **Scaffolding** - Hints available when needed
7. **Real-World Context** - Actual network scenarios

### **Common Mistakes Addressed**

âŒ **Allocating small subnets first** â†’ Causes fragmentation
âœ… **Solution:** Game enforces largest-first ordering

âŒ **Choosing wrong subnet mask** â†’ Waste or shortage
âœ… **Solution:** Auto-calculates optimal mask

âŒ **Creating overlaps** â†’ Address conflicts
âœ… **Solution:** Automatic overlap detection

âŒ **Not understanding efficiency** â†’ Excessive waste
âœ… **Solution:** Real-time efficiency scoring

